The paper deals with the problem of unifying knowledge from multiple classifiers with different architectures and target classes into a single classifier. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given that the paper focuses on image classification tasks and proposes a method based on knowledge distillation, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG and cs.CV.
